Aside from facilitating the computation of Bayes factors, the default priors also satisfy a number of desirable theoretical consistency conditions, which will be elaborated below (Rouder & Morey, 2012; Rouder et al., 2009, 2012; Wetzels et al., 2012). That being said, they also possess features that strike us as undesirable: 
One of the goals of the default prior on effect sizes is to capture the beliefs surrounding the alternative hypothesis \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
